<div id="review_114638753" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/114638753" />
    <a title="Tricia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1023870-tricia"><img alt="Tricia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1208268123p2/1023870.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/114638753?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tricia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tricia" href="/user/show/1023870-tricia">Tricia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1023870-tricia?shelf=audio">audio</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer114638753" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4703666053684144800">Part critique of how the Buddha&apos;s teachings have been packaged into an inaccessible, esoteric <i>ism</i> and part &quot;how to&quot; guide for &quot;dharma practice,&quot; that is, meditation and pondering life and death. I like the repeated focus on integrity and I&apos;ve found that word useful when thinking about my eating habits and interactions with others. The book complements my current yoga practice, which thanks to the teacher&apos;s guidance, has become more of a moving meditation than it has been in the past. I don&apos;t fee</span>
  <span id="freeText4703666053684144800" style="display:none">Part critique of how the Buddha's teachings have been packaged into an inaccessible, esoteric <i>ism</i> and part "how to" guide for "dharma practice," that is, meditation and pondering life and death. I like the repeated focus on integrity and I've found that word useful when thinking about my eating habits and interactions with others. The book complements my current yoga practice, which thanks to the teacher's guidance, has become more of a moving meditation than it has been in the past. I don't feel this book needs to be read front to back, like I did this first time, but could instead be a quick soothing reference. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4703666053684144800" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


